President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key roles promoting U.S. foreign policy and national security. The nominees include Mark Brzezinski for Ambassador to Poland, Elizabeth Anne Noseworthy Fitzsimmons for Ambassador to the Togolese Republic, Rebecca Eliza Gonzales for Director of the Office of Foreign Missions, Brian Wesley Shukan for Ambassador to Benin, David John Young for Ambassador to Malawi, Adriana Kugler for U.S. Executive Director of the International Bank for Reconstruction and Development, Oren Whyche-Shaw for U.S. Director of the African Development Bank, Corey Hinderstein for Deputy Administrator for Defense Nuclear Nonproliferation at the Department of Energy, and David Honey for Deputy Under Secretary for Research and Engineering at the Department of Defense. These individuals have diverse backgrounds and experiences in various government and international roles.